<li>D&rsquo;Ancona Costa, Cristina, 1992,
&ldquo;&Alpha;&mu;&omicron;&rho;&#981;&omicron;&nu;
&Kappa;&alpha;&iota;
&Alpha;&nu;&epsilon;&iota;&delta;&epsilon;&omicron;&nu;.
Causalit&eacute; des Formes et Causalit&eacute; de l&rsquo;un chez
Plotin&rdquo;, <em>Revue de Philosophie Ancienne</em>, 10(1):
69&ndash;113.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1997, &ldquo;Separation and the Forms: A
Plotinian Approach&rdquo;, <em>American Catholic Philosophical
Quarterly</em>, 71(3): 367&ndash;403. doi:10.5840/acpq199771334</li>

<li>Emilsson, Eyj&oacute;lfur Kjalar, 1991, &ldquo;Plotinus and
Soul-Body Dualism&rdquo;, in <em>Psychology</em> (Companions to
Ancient Thought 2), Stephen Everson (ed.), Cambridge/New York:
Cambridge University Press, 148&ndash;165.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2019, &ldquo;Plotinus&rsquo; Doctrine of
Badness as Matter in Ennead I.8 [51]&rdquo;, in <em>Platonism and
Christian Thought in Late Antiquity</em>, Panagiotis G. Pavlos, Lars
Fredrik Janby, Eyj&oacute;lfur Kjalar Emilsson, and Torstein Theodor
Tollefsen (eds), Abingdon/New York: Routledge, 78&ndash;99.</li>

<li>Gertz, Sebastian, 2022, &ldquo;Plotinus, Gnosticism, and
Christianity&rdquo;, in
 <a href="#GW2022">Gerson and Wilberding 2022</a>:
 41&ndash;64 (ch. 4). doi:10.1017/9781108770255.003</li>

<li>Hadot, Pierre, 1960, &ldquo;&Ecirc;tre, Vie, Pens&eacute;e chez
Plotin et avant Plotin&rdquo;, in <em>Les sources de Plotin</em>
(Entretiens sur l&rsquo;antiquit&eacute; classique 5), Gen&egrave;ve:
Fondation Hardt, 105&ndash;141.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1980, &ldquo;Les niveaux de conscience dans
les &eacute;tats mystiques selon Plotin. [Levels of consciousness in
Plotin&rsquo;s mystical states.]&rdquo;, <em>Journal de Psychologie
Normale et Pathologique</em>, 77(2&ndash;3): 243&ndash;266.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1982, &ldquo;L&rsquo; &laquo; amour
Magicien&#8239;&raquo;. aux Origenes de la Notion de
&laquo;&#8239;magia Naturalis&#8239;&raquo;: Platon, Plotin, Marsile
Ficin&rdquo;, <em>Revue Philosophique de La France et de
l&rsquo;&Eacute;tranger</em>, 172(2): 283&ndash;292.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1987, &ldquo;L&rsquo;union de
l&rsquo;&acirc;me avec l&rsquo;intellect divin dans
l&rsquo;exp&eacute;rience mystique plotinienne&rdquo;, in <em>Proclus
et son influence: actes du colloque de Neuch&acirc;tel, juin
1985</em>, Gilbert Boss and Gerhard Seel (eds), Z&uuml;rich:
&Eacute;ditions du Grand Midi, 3&ndash;27.</li>

<li>Hutchinson, D. M., 2022, &ldquo;Composition of Sensible
Bodies&rdquo;, in
 <a href="#GW2022">Gerson and Wilberding 2022</a>:
 289&ndash;311 (ch. 12). doi:10.1017/9781108770255.013</li>

<li>Igal, Jes&uacute;s, 1979, &ldquo;Arist&oacute;teles y la
evoluci&oacute;n de la antropolog&iacute;a de Plotino&rdquo;,
<em>Pensamiento: Revista de investigaci&oacute;n e Informaci&oacute;n
filos&oacute;fica</em>, 35(138): 315&ndash;346.</li>

<li>Kalligas, Paul, 1997, &ldquo;Forms of Individuals in Plotinus: A
Re-Examination&rdquo;, <em>Phronesis</em>, 42(2): 206&ndash;227.
doi:10.1163/156852897762700106</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2011, &ldquo;The Structure of Appearances:
Plotinus on the Constitution of Sensible Objects&rdquo;, <em>The
Philosophical Quarterly</em>, 61(245): 762&ndash;782.
doi:10.1111/j.1467-9213.2011.702.x</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2012, &ldquo;From &lsquo;Energeia&rsquo; to
Energy: Plotinus and the Formation of the Concept of Energy&rdquo;,
<em>Hermathena</em>, 192: 45&ndash;64.</li>

<li>Lloyd, A. C., 1990, <em>The Anatomy of Neoplatonism</em>, Oxford:
Oxford University Press. doi:10.1093/0198238061.001.0001</li>

<li>Menn, Stephen, 2001, &ldquo;Plotinus on the Identity of Knowledge
with Its Object&rdquo;, <em>Apeiron</em>, 34(3): 233&ndash;246.
doi:10.1515/APEIRON.2001.34.3.233</li>

<li>O&rsquo;Brien, Denis, 1977, &ldquo;Le volontaire et la
n&eacute;cessit&eacute;&#8239;: r&eacute;flexions sur la descente de
l&rsquo;&acirc;me dans la philosophie de Plotin&rdquo;, <em>Revue
Philosophique de la France et de l&rsquo;&Eacute;tranger</em>, 167(4):
401&ndash;422.</li>

<li>O&rsquo;Meara, Dominic J., 1980, &ldquo;The Problem of
Omnipresence in Plotinus Ennead VI, 4-5: A Reply&rdquo;,
<em>Dionysius</em>, 4: 61&ndash;73.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1990, &ldquo;Le probl&egrave;me du discours
sur l&rsquo;indicible chez Plotin&rdquo;, <em>Revue de
Th&eacute;ologie et de Philosophie</em>, 122(2): 145&ndash;156.</li>

<li>O&rsquo;Meara, Dominic J., 1996, &ldquo;The Hierarchical Ordering
of Reality in Plotinus&rdquo;, in
 <a href="#Gerson1996">Gerson 1996</a>:
 66&ndash;81 (ch. 3). doi:10.1017/CCOL0521470935.004</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2000, &ldquo;Scepticism and Ineffability in
Plotinus&rdquo;, <em>Phronesis</em>, 45(3): 240&ndash;251.
doi:10.1163/156852800510207</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2022, &ldquo;Love in Plotinus&rsquo;
Thought&rdquo;, in <em>Platonic Love from Antiquity to the
Renaissance</em>, Carl S&eacute;an O&rsquo;Brien and John Dillon
(eds), Cambridge/New York: Cambridge University Press, 111&ndash;124.
doi:10.1017/9781108525596.009</li>

<li>Remes, Pauliina, 2005, &ldquo;Plotinus On The Unity And Identity
Of Changing Particulars&rdquo;, in <em>Oxford Studies In Ancient
Philosophy XXVIII</em>, David Sedley (ed.), Oxford: Oxford University
Press, 273&ndash;302. doi:10.1093/oso/9780199281930.003.0010</li>

<li>Rist, John M., 1983, &ldquo;Metaphysics and Psychology in
Plotinus&rsquo; Treatment of the Soul&rdquo;, in <em>Graceful Reason:
Essays in Ancient and Medieval Philosophy Presented to Joseph Owens,
CSSR, on the Occasion of His Seventy-Fifth Birthday and the Fiftieth
Anniversary of His Ordination</em> (Papers in Mediaeval Studies 4),
Lloyd P. Gerson (ed.), Toronto, Ont: Pontifical Institute of Mediaeval
Studies, 135&ndash;151 (ch. 7).</li>

<li>Schroeder, Frederic M., 1987, &ldquo;Synousia, Synaisthaesis and
Synesis: Presence and Dependence in the Plotinian Philosophy of
Consciousness&rdquo;, in <em>Philosophie, Wissenschaften, Technik.
Philosophie (Historische Einleitung; Platonismus)</em> (Aufstieg und
Niedergang der R&ouml;mischen Welt, II 36.1), Wolfgang Haase (ed.),
Berlin/Boston: De Gruyter, 677&ndash;699.
doi:10.1515/9783110861570-016</li>

<li>Strange, Steven K., 1994, &ldquo;Plotinus on the Nature of
Eternity and Time&rdquo;, in <em>Aristotle in Late Antiquity</em>
(Studies in Philosophy and the History of Philosophy 27), Lawrence P.
Schrenk (ed.), Washington, DC: Catholic University of America Press,
22&ndash;53.</li>

<li>Tornau, Christian, 1998, &ldquo;Wissenschaft, Seele, Geist. Zur
Bedeutung einer Analogie bei Plotin (Enn. IV 9,5 und VI 2,20)&rdquo;,
<em>G&ouml;ttinger Forum f&uuml;r Altertumswissenschaft</em>, 1:
87&ndash;111. doi:10.14628/GFA.1998.0.77012</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2009, &ldquo;Qu&rsquo; est-ce qu&rsquo;un
individu? Unit&eacute;, individualit&eacute; et conscience de soi dans
la m&eacute;taphysique plotinienne de l&rsquo;&acirc;me&rdquo;,
<em>Les &Eacute;tudes Philophiques</em>, 2009(3): 333&ndash;60.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2016, &ldquo;Seelenspur und
Aufnahmef&auml;higkeit: ein plotinischer Zirkel?&rdquo;, in <em>Seele
und Materie im Neuplatonismus</em> (Heidelberger Forschungen 39), Jens
Halfwassen, Tobias Dangel, and Carl O&rsquo;Brien (eds), Heidelberg:
Winter, 135&ndash;160.</li>

<li>Tuominen, Miira, 2022, &ldquo;Virtue and Happiness&rdquo;, in
 <a href="#GW2022">Gerson and Wilberding 2022</a>:
 363&ndash;385 (ch. 15). doi:10.1017/9781108770255.016</li>

<li>Wilberding, James, 2008, &ldquo;Automatic Action in
Plotinus&rdquo;, in <em>Oxford Studies in Ancient Philosophy</em>,
David Sedley (ed.), Oxford: Oxford University Press, 373&ndash;408.
doi:10.1093/oso/9780199544875.003.0011</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="CRefe">C. Reference</h3>

<ul class="hanging">

<li>Blumenthal, H. J., 1987, &ldquo;Plotinus in the Light of Twenty
Years&rsquo; Scholarship, 1951 &ndash; 1971&rdquo;, in
<em>Philosophie, Wissenschaften, Technik. Philosophie (Historische
Einleitung; Platonismus)</em> (Aufstieg und Niedergang der
r&ouml;mischen Welt, II 36.1), Wolfgang Haase (ed.), Berlin/Boston: De
Gruyter, 528&ndash;570. doi:10.1515/9783110861570-013</li>

<li>Corrigan, Kevin, 1987, &ldquo;The Course of Plotinian Scholarship
from 1971 to 1986&rdquo;, in <em>Philosophie, Wissenschaften, Technik.
Philosophie (Historische Einleitung; Platonismus)</em> (Aufstieg und
Niedergang der r&ouml;mischen Welt, II 36.1), Wolfgang Haase (ed.),
Berlin/Boston: De Gruyter, 571&ndash;623.
doi:10.1515/9783110861570-014</li>

